  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mifumi Model on Violence and Abuse - Bridging Fund</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Uganda, the rate of violence and abuse against women at 68% is extremely high. Despite this, conviction rates for the crime remain appallingly low at less than 6%. Due to poor support services and weak community sanctions against abuse, women who experience domestic violence (DV) across Tororo district, and their children, remain vulnerable and underserved. Through this project, they will be helped to recover physically, mentally, and economically from the violence, and supported to have safer lives with prospects of better livelihoods. The project will provide a range of services for affected women and their families, which will lead to a reduction in the impact and number of incidences of domestic violence across the district and more widely in Uganda. As a result of the project, women directly affected, and their children will have better lives, and Mifumi will have strengthened its systems and improved its learning about how to replicate its model of working.</narrative>
  </description>
